<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-589-253  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 589 253.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Nov 6 1990 v4 n38 p10(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Praxitel says 'Read My Lips' in word processing, DTP programs.andO;(Praxitel Inc.'s Read My Lips data entry software) (desktoppublishing) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cohen, Raines.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Praxitel Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Read My Lips (Multimedia software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionVoice RecognitionData EntrySoftware PackagesDesktop Publishing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Raines CohenandM;Ypsilanti, Mich.andP;  -- Now that your Mac has a microphone, what do you do withit?andP;  Praxitel Inc. this week announced a product that adds voice-annotationcapabilities to several word processors and a page-layout application.andM;Read My Lips, a Control Panel device (cdev), lets users add SoundNotes todocuments in Claris Corp.'s MacWrite II and Version 4.6, Microsoft Word 4.0,Paragon Concepts Inc.'s Nisus, WordPerfect 1.0.5, and Aldus Corp.'s PageMaker4.0.andM;When a user records a sound or selects a prerecorded sound for annotation,the Startup document (INIT) pastes a user-selected voice-note icon into thedocument to indicate which sound is attached where.andP;  The sounds, which areembedded in the file, can be played back even when a document is convertedbetween applications; a play-only version of the software can be freelydistributed.andM;The initial version of the $119 program, due to ship next month, supportsonly Farallon Computing Inc.'s MacRecorder and VoiceRecorder digitizers; thecompany said future releases will add support for the built-in microphones onthe Macintosh IIsi and LC, as well as other devices using the new soundmanager in System 6.0.7.andM;Praxitel Inc. is at 1631 Sheffield Drive, Ypsilanti, Mich.andP;  48198.andP;  Phone(313) 485-6278; fax (313) 487-5349.andO;</TEXT></DOC>